Macy","remark":"Ins premium charged from owners."},{"modifiedDate":"2023-11-01T12:37:02.767","modifiedByFull":"Butcher, Carol","remark":"Removed Sabine/Neches Waterway User Fee $7,600 (Port Arthur) as it is no longer a Charterer\u0027s account item in WS"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-09-27T16:50:26.22","modifiedByFull":"Mohlin, Max","remark":"Operator comments: Voyage generated basis Houston to Pajaritos but turned out to load Port Arthur and discharge Tuxpan followed by Veracruz. We were initially instructed to proceed to Houston where Captain tendered readiness on the 28th Aug as per CVC terms. Later that day, PMI changed load port to Port Arthur where the commercial laycan was 3-5 Sep but the vessel didn\u0027t berth until the 8th Sep. With other words, vessel was on demurrage well before she even started loading. We billed 15.78 days demurrage @ $39,900 which is the main factor improving the PnL of this voyage. The additional disport in ECMEX resulted in an additional $63k lumpsum freight. Longer voyage than expected hence higher bunker cost, however looking at the cons/day vessel performed well compared to estimates. Besides getting the BLs signed at the last minute, which seems to be quite normal with these short voyages, not much to mention operationally."},{"modifiedDate":"2023-09-21T19:57:48.08","modifiedByFull":"Mohlin, Max","remark":"departure bunkers Veracruz updated"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-09-14T20:56:36.333","modifiedByFull":"Mohlin, Max","remark":"additional disport  (freight updated) - demurrage estimated"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-09-06T20:17:54.18","modifiedByFull":"Mohlin, Max","remark":"Berthing delays in Port Arthur - Demurrage estimated"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-08-29T13:43:06.887","modifiedByFull":"Dragheim, Carsten Bo","remark":"CVE 01/09-16/09 added as misc. expense (500,-)"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-08-29T13:42:59.78","modifiedByFull":"Hasbo, Gustav","remark":"Port Arthur nominated as load port instead of Houston."},{"modifiedDate":"2023-08-28T19:56:49.6